title: Princess Eugenie's godmother filmed whipping protester
text:
Princess Eugenie's godmother filmed whipping protester By Brandon Livesay 
A British royal has allegedly used a whip to slash at a foxhunt protester during a fiery confrontation. 
Princess Eugenie's godmother Lulu Hutley was filmed by the Guildford Hunt Saboteurs at a hunt on Slades Farm in Guildford on Saturday afternoon. 
Hutley, the joint master of the Surrey Union Hunt, was furious with campaigners who interrupted her ride. 
The socialite is seen in the video using her riding crop to apparently lash out at one of the "Saboteurs," named as Conor Macleod. 
"While the hunt looped around a few times in an attempt to lose us, sabs tried to get to the nearest road and were rammed against a fence and then struck with a whip by Lulu Hutley," the group posted on its Facebook page. 
A Surrey Union Hunt spokesperson claims the video was taken out of context. 
"You can clearly see Lulu is holding the whip upside-down in order to hit the gate, not the person," a spokesperson said. 
"She saw the protester was trapped between the horse and the gate and was trying to make a noise by banging on the gate to get the horse to back off. 
"It was quick thinking by one of our Masters in a dangerous situation and it’s terribly sad it’s being misrepresented." 
The matter has been reported to Surrey police and is under investigation, the Mirror reports . © Nine Digital Pty Ltd 2017
